{
  "texts": [
    "RL typically involves defining a reward function, selecting an appropriate RL algorithm (e.g., Q-learning, Deep Q Networks), and fine-tuning the agent's policies through repeated interactions.",
    "While RL has been successful in various applications, it comes with challenges like the exploration-exploitation trade-off and can require significant computational resources and time.",
    "The key advantage of the RL model is that the training can be done even in sparse environments where few or no examples are available.",
    "It is especially suitable for sequential decision-making (Lutz et al. 2023).",
    "Deep learning is focused on artificial neural networks (ANN) with multiple layers (deep neural networks)."
  ]
}